snippet: The government signed a peace deal with the M23 rebels it had been fighting until they laid down their arms last month, ending weeks of wrangling over the terms of an agreement.
abstract: Democratic Republic of Congo signs peace deal with M23 rebels it had been fighting until they laid down their arms, ending weeks of wrangling over the terms of the agreement.
